  <article id="section-anatomy">
    <h1 class="app-article-headline hca-typography--headline">Anatomy and Types</h1>
    <section id="section-anatomy-and-types" class="app-section">
      {{!-- <h2 class="hca-typography--title">Anatomy of a Dialog</h2> --}}
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-sm-6">
          <div class="hca-layout__container--body-content">
            <span class="hca-typography--body-2">Optional Title</span>
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Dialogs may have an optional title that concisely describes the type of decision being made. </p>
            <p class="hca-typography--support">NOTE: Titles must always be visible in their entirety. They should not overflow or ellipsis.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="hca-layout__container--body-content">
            <span class="hca-typography--body-2">Content</span>
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Dialog content typically consists of text and/or UI control elements. It is focused on a specific task, such as confirming item deletion or choosing a setting.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="hca-layout__container--body-content">
            <span class="hca-typography--body-2">Action Bar</span>
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Dialogs should always have an action bar that has at least one action that acknowledges/dismisses the dialog, but can contain both affirmative and dismissive actions.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-5">
          <figure class="hca-visual-example">
            <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/components/dialogs/anatomy.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="Anatomy of a Dialog" />
            <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption hca-typography--caption">Anatomy of a Dialog</figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>

  <article id="section-alerts">
    <section class="app-section">
      <h2 class="hca-typography--title">Alerts</h2>
      <div class="row app-section">
        <div class="col-sm-6">
          <div class="hca-layout__container--body-content">
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Alerts are urgent interruptions, requiring user acknowledgement, that inform the user about a situation.</p>
            <p class="hca-typography--support">NOTE: Alert dialogs have a different use case than Snackbars. Snackbars present optional information after an action, such as confirming the deletion of data. They often allow a user to undo an action that was just taken.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="app-section">
        <h3 class="hca-typography--body-2">Alerts without title bars</h3>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-4">
            <div class="hca-layout__container--body-content">
              <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Most alerts do not need titles.</p>
              <p class="hca-typography--body-1">They should summarize a decision concisely by either:
                <ul class="app-list app-list--bulleted">
                  <li class="app-list__item">Asking a question (i.e. "Delete this item?")</li>
                  <li class="app-list__item">Making a statement related to the action buttons</li>
                </ul>
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-sm-8">
            <div class="row">
              <div class="col-sm-6">
                <figure class="hca-visual-example hca-visual-example--do">
                  <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/components/dialogs/alert-no-title.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="Visual example of an Alert with no title" />
                  <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption hca-typography--caption">The affirmative action "Discard" describes the outcome of the user's decision.</figcaption>
                </figure>
              </div>
              <div class="col-sm-6">
                <figure class="hca-visual-example hca-visual-example--dont">
                  <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/components/dialogs/alert-no-title-dont.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="Visual example of what NOT to do with an alert" />
                  <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption hca-typography--caption">The dismissive action "No" is unclear as to what happens after a user selects it. "Cancel" or "Go back" would be more descriptive.</figcaption>
                </figure>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="app-section">
        <h3 class="hca-typography--body-2">Alerts with title bars</h3>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-5">
            <div class="hca-layout__container--body-content">
              <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Use title bar alerts only for high-risk situations, such as the potential loss of connectivity. Users should be able to understand the choices based on the title and button text alone.</p>
              <p class="hca-typography--body-1">If a title is required:
                <ul class="app-list app-list--bulleted">
                  <li class="app-list__item">Use a clear question or statement with an explanation in the content area, such as "Send health record unencrypted?"</li>
                  <li class="app-list__item">Avoid apologies, ambiguity, or questions, such as “Warning!” or “Are you sure?”</li>
                </ul>
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-sm-7">
            <div class="row">
              <div class="col-sm-6">
                <figure class="hca-visual-example hca-visual-example--do">
                  <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/components/dialogs/alert-with-title.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="Good example of dialog with title" />
                  <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption hca-typography--caption">This dialog presents a specific question, provides clear actions, and concisely communicates the impact that the action will have.</figcaption>
                </figure>
              </div>
              <div class="col-sm-6">
                <figure class="hca-visual-example hca-visual-example--dont">
                  <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/components/dialogs/alert-with-title-dont.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="Bad example of dialog with title" />
                  <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption hca-typography--caption">This dialog presents an ambiguous question, and its scope of impact is unclear.</figcaption>
                </figure>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
