            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Simple Dialogs are called "simple" simply because they only take one single action to move on from.</p>
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">They present multiple options to the user, and close immediately upon the user making their selection. They should only be utilized in scenarios where the user is making a single selection from multiple options, and there is no further exploration to be made about these options.</p>
            <p class="hca-typography--support">NOTE: Simple Dialogs may have a "cancel" button as to provide a clear option for the user to dismiss, but they should not have any sort of confirmation button. The user's selection immediately confirms their choice.</p>
